SANI KUKASHEKA USMAN : Troops of Operation LAFIYA DOLE on Sunday 16th December 2018 neutralised four Boko Haram terrorists and recover weapons. The terrorists came at about 5.00pm to attack Maibukarti village along Maiduguri-Damboa road when they were engaged by the gallant troops. <img class="alignleft  wp-image-71358" src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-amunition-420x280.jpeg" alt="" width="378" height="252" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-amunition-420x280.jpeg 420w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-amunition-150x100.jpeg 150w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-amunition-768x512.jpeg 768w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-amunition-720x480.jpeg 720w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-amunition.jpeg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 378px) 100vw, 378px" />        The troops were further reinforced and went on hot pursuit of the fleeing terrorists, while the Nigerian Air Forces provided close air support. Unfortunately, one soldier paid the supreme price during the encounter with the terrorists. The gallant troops recovered 4 AK-47 rifles, 45 roun<img class="wp-image-71359 alignleft" src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-bikes-420x280.jpeg" alt="" width="384" height="256" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-bikes-420x280.jpeg 420w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-bikes-150x100.jpeg 150w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-bikes-768x512.jpeg 768w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-bikes-720x480.jpeg 720w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Boko-Haram-bikes.jpeg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px" />ds of 7.62mm ammunition, 5 AK-47 rifrles magazine, 2 Motorcycles and 1 bicycles. Other items recovered include 1 Bandolier, 1 GSM handset, 3 SIM cards, an earpiece, some phone accessories, kolanuts, gloves and drugs. The exploitation continues in conjunction with CJTF.      SANI KUKASHEKA USMAN Brigadier General Director Army Public Relations Innocent Korie is an ICT and Project Management Professional with very good flair in business development, and social media management. He has a degree in Electronic & Computer Engineering. He is currently stationed at the Online Unit of Nigerian Television Authority